Class Track

  • Object
    • Track
  • public class Track
extends Object
    The Track class represents a track. Each track has a title, artist, play time, and file path. Here is an example of how a track can be created. 
     Track track = new Track("Holiday", "Green Day", "American Idiot", 232);
    Here is an example of how a track can be used. 
     System.out.println("Artist: " + track.getArtist());
 System.out.println(track);
    Version:
    Spring 2023
    Author:
    CS121 Instructors
